_description: John Skelton, The garlande of Laurell — 1604 lines, chiefly in rhyme royal

BLCottVitEX.First Lines:
Arectynge my syght toward the zodiakThe siggnys twelue for to
                    behold afar…
BLCottVitEX.Last Lines:
…Of laureat promocion your place is here ReservydWe wille
                    vnderstande how ye have it deservid
BLCottVitEX.Note:
Imperfect at end due to damage to MS. Folio number reflects the most
                    recent foliation.
